    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Kinderhook Lake, once called Wogasawoochuk or “Big Fish Lake” by the Mohican, sits on peat-rich soil that fed many orchards.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
